Present Perfect and Simple Past

We can use the present perfect and the simple past when describing a past event that is connected to the present.

We usually use the present perfect to introduce the topic but use in the simple past to provide the details of what happened. 

I've had two jobs.
(persent perfect)

My first job was at a restaurant.
(simple past)

I've been to Canada three times.
(present perfect)

The last time I went to Canada, I visited Toronto. 
(simple past)

She's won the championship twice. 
(present perfect)

Last year, she won very easily.
(simple past)

